This paper deals with image classification using neural networks, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The use of recurrent neural networks (RNNs) and patch-based approaches suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also deals with remote sensing data, which suggests that it may be relevant to the information retrieval (cs.IR) and graphics (cs.GR) sub-categories.
